Noscitur a sociis • /nosәtәr èy sówsiyәs/. Literally, "It is known from its associates." A term applied in interpretation of statutory law. Under the doctrine of "noscitur a sociis" the questionable meaning of a word or doubtful words can be derived from its association with other words within the context of the phrase.